<br>
I don't know about Freeport, but Lashun Novashine in Qeynos didn't attack me, nor did any of the priestly types that wander karana or qeynos.  Noone else I encountered there did either, but I didn't wander into the paladin/cleric guild and offer to buy 'em a drink either.<br>
<br>
There is an easy way to raise faction with good elves... Crushbone!  As long as you don't care about going into the Indigo Brotherhood I guess...I know lots of dark elves that are KOS there, and they LIVE in Neriak.  Dark Elf faction is easy to gain with the help of others, or used to be anyways, by getting someone in Third Gate REAL drunk off wine.<br>
<br>
It's not that places are impossible to raise faction (some are of course), it's just that sometimes it's improbable.  Killing Bugglegup (sp) in Steamfont gained me Basher Faction, so theoretically it may be possible for me to kill it, the troll slayers, and Lynuga enough to enter Grobb.  Not sure about Oggok faction, but I hear more people complain about raising grobb faction.  I guess some of the factions are impossible to raise, but if you can just raise basher faction, then at least you can bind within the city without fear of chain deaths when you return to your bind.<br>
<br>
And correct me if I'm wrong anyone, but you're threatening to all wolves and bears unless you're a ranger, druid, or beastlord.  If they attack you and Holly Windstalker or druids at druid rings are around, they will attack you.<br>
<br>
I wish more humans would follow Bertox...I hate hearing people whine about not being able to see.  Carry a frickin' light source and turn your clipping plane up!<br>
<br>
Heretics are godly easy to raise faction with, and it isn't hard to raise Erudin faction to the point where you can walk through the town, albeit carefully.<br>
<br>
I hear the greenbloods in Butcherblock make a nice way to raise dwarf faction, and I know the aqua goblins in BB and in OOT are good for that.  Once you get to a certain level of acceptance in most places, you can do quests that will shoot you up to amiable in no time.  I slew kobolds in the warrens, all green to me at 18, and in no time I was dubious.  Found the NPC to hand kobold molars to, turned in about 3 backpacks worth, and suddenly i was amiable to everyone and their brother.  Erudin faction can be worked on by killing heretics in Toxxulia.<br>
<br>
Eh...just some stuff that's useless to ya now.  Oh, and being level 9 and running out of mana fast isn't amazingly odd, btw, no matter what wisdom or int you have as your base (if you aren't twinked I'm guessing).  My gnome necro has like 137 wisdom or so with a little jewelry, and he still runs out of mana pretty fast casting my level 4 spells.  I'm guessing if you're using your level 8 spells at level 9 they're gonna be a pretty big drain on ya.<br>
<br>
Oh well, hope you enjoy your ranger or bard!  Wave sometime so we can tell ya apart from all the others! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A> at: 8/10/02 1:58:59 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarkitip.showPublicProfile?language=EN>arkitip</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 355<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/10/02 12:45:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> faction</span><hr size=1> You can raise faction in a lot of those places you mentioned. It's tedious, but do-able. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urhaxalygen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhaxalygen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/10/02 12:10:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> More thoughts on a Bertoxx Cleric...</span><hr size=1> I found myself playing a newbie ranger on Terris-Thule<br>
